    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="367"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d367">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/967½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_WW1" type="from"
                            >Wilson</persName> to the Special Representative</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_HEM1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">House</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 1, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The resolution you suggest is entirely in line with my thought and has my
                    approval. You will realize how unfortunate it would be for the conference to
                    discuss peace terms in a spirit antagonistic to my January address to the
                    Senate. Our people and Congress will not fight for any selfish aim on the part
                    of any belligerent, with the possible exception of Alsace-Lorraine, least of all
                    for divisions of territory such as have been contemplated in Asia Minor. I think
                    it will be obvious to all that it would be a fatal mistake to cool the ardour of
                    America. Answering your cable after conferring with <persName corresp="#p_CG1"
                        >Clemenceau</persName>,<note n="1" xml:id="d367fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_318">p. 318</ref>.</note> I
                    favour the most effective war council obtainable whether directed by one man or
                    not.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
